<section xml:id="section-scalar-triang-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p><dl width="narrow">

	<li>
	<title>scalar-triangular form</title>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>scalar-triangular</h></idx>
	<idx>scalar-triangular form</idx>
	<idx><h>form</h><h>scalar-triangular</h></idx>
	<p> an upper or lower triangular matrix that has the same value repeated down the main diagonal </p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

<p> The remaining terminology and notation are relative to a square matrix <m>A</m> and a specific eigenvalue <m>\lambda</m> for that matrix. </p>

<p><dl width="narrow">

	<li xml:id="definition-scalar-triang-gen-eigenvec">
	<title>generalized eigenvector</title>
	<idx><h>generalized</h><h>eigenvector</h></idx>
	<idx><h>eigenvector</h><h>generalized</h></idx>
	<p>
		a nonzero vector that is in the null space of the matrix
		<m>(\lambda I - A)^k</m>
		for some positive integer <m>k</m>
	</p>
	</li>

	<li xml:id="definition-scalar-triang-gen-eigenspace">
	<title>generalized eigenspace</title>
	<idx><h>generalized</h><h>eigenspace</h></idx>
	<idx><h>eigenspace</h><h>generalized</h></idx>
	<p>
	the collection of all generalized eigenvectors for <m>A</m> corresponding to <m>\lambda</m>,
	along with the zero vector;
	denoted <m>G_{\lambda}(A)</m>
	</p>
	</li>

	<li xml:id="definition-scalar-triang-eigensubspace">
	<title>generalized eigensubspace of degree <m>k</m></title>
	<idx><h>generalized</h><h>eigensubspace</h></idx>
	<p> the nullspace of the matrix <m>(\lambda I - A)^k</m>; denoted <m>E^k_{\lambda}(A)</m> </p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
